      "side": 1,
      "message": "Go always initializes values to their so-called \"zero value\". For ints, it\u0027s 0.\n\nBut, the above doesn\u0027t matter:\nby **default** if a Go func returns non-nil error, then other returned values must be ignored.\nHence, this func can return \"-123, 42, \u003cnon-nil-error\u003e\" and still be correct.",
